I am having same problem trying to export RetinaNet (https://github.com/kuangliu/pytorch-retinanet). Can you get this to run?

import torch
import torch.onnx
from torch import nn
from torch.autograd import Variable
import torch.nn.functional as F

class SimpleNet(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self):
        super(SimpleNet, self).__init__()
        
    def forward(self, x):
        h1 = x
        h2 = F.interpolate(x, size=h1.size()[-2:], mode='bilinear', align_corners=False)
        h = torch.cat([h1, h2], dim=1)
        return h

model = SimpleNet()
x = Variable(torch.randn(1, 3, 10, 10)).cpu()
torch_out = torch.onnx._export(model, x, '~/temp/test_bilinear_onnx_export.txt', export_params=True, verbose=True)
print('finished onnx export')

I am having same problem trying to export RetinaNet (https://github.com/kuangliu/pytorch-retinanet). Can you get this to run?

```
import torch
import torch.onnx
from torch import nn
from torch.autograd import Variable
import torch.nn.functional as F

class SimpleNet(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self):
        super(SimpleNet, self).__init__()
        
    def forward(self, x):
        h1 = x
        h2 = F.interpolate(x, size=h1.size()[-2:], mode='bilinear', align_corners=False)
        h = torch.cat([h1, h2], dim=1)
        return h

model = SimpleNet()
x = Variable(torch.randn(1, 3, 10, 10)).cpu()
torch_out = torch.onnx._export(model, x, '~/temp/test_bilinear_onnx_export.txt', export_params=True, verbose=True)
print('finished onnx export')
```
